YouTube Classification Thinking (Key Insights)
The YouTube classifiers embody the right philosophy:

Layered approach: Rules → LLM → Fallback
Content-type awareness: Distinguishes /watch?v=, /shorts/, /channel/, homepage
Usefulness vs Category: A video can be GAMING category but EDUCATIONAL usefulness (e.g., "Coding in Minecraft")
Context-rich prompts: LLM gets title, channel, description, duration, view count, etc.
Heuristic priors: Pre-compute hints like "likely_entertainment" before LLM call
Graceful degradation: If LLM fails, fall back to rules; if rules fail, default to UNKNOWN (allow)
